  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bring Back Native Stingless Bees, Empower Women</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We aim to train 30 local Maya women to raise melipona, native stingless bees that live in hollow logs, produce rich, curative honey, and have historically been an object of worship and a staple of the local economy. In the past 25 years, more than 90% of stingless bee colonies have disappeared, due to deforestation and the introduction of African bees. Our goal is to donate hives to 10 communities and train women in beekeeping. If we lose the melipona, we lose a cultural and financial treasure.</narrative>
  </description>
